  "executive_summary": "Acne Studios operates at the intersection of fashion house and cultural institution, producing clothing that functions as both wardrobe and artistic statement. The brand's visual language centers on a palette of non-colors\u2014gallery whites, concrete grays, occasional sand\u2014deployed across relaxed silhouettes that shift between oversized and fitted without committing to either extreme. This studied ambiguity extends to their product range: distressed denim sits alongside refined leather goods, heritage sportswear adjacent to conceptual basics. The audience comprises urban twenty-to-thirty-somethings who parse fashion through an art-historical lens, seeking pieces that signal cultural literacy rather than wealth. They understand the irony in $400 distressed jeans and appreciate the reference when a plaid boxer becomes gallery object.",
  "one_line_positioning": "Fashion house treating garments as cultural artifacts for an art-literate urban audience.",
